####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### "Shandong" is transferred into the list

China's first completely domestically produced aircraft carrier, also the second aircraft carrier in active duty, was officially delivered on Tuesday (December 17), and announced its name "Shandong". Xi Jinping, the supreme leader of the Chinese party, government, and military, attended the transfer ceremony held in a military port in Sanya, Hainan.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/51710054_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### Shandong Ship, Way No. 17

The Central Military Commission of the Communist Party of China was officially named "Shandong Ship of the Chinese People's Liberation Army" for this "big ship" and the port number was "17". On the day of the transfer, about 5,000 officers and soldiers of the Chinese Navy and aircraft carrier construction units attended the celebration ceremony.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/51706715_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### Shandong? Taiwan?

Earlier, the major military forums in China were rumored to be named "Shandong", but this statement has never been officially confirmed. A well -known portion of China has also held an online survey to solicit opinions on the name of the first domestic aircraft carrier. As a result, the "Taiwan" was supported by the most people.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38590715_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### Accept baptism

The "Shandong" held a water -laid -laidation ceremony at the Dalian Shipyard Construction Factory of China Shipbuilding Heavy Industry Corporation on April 26, 2017. At that time, the aircraft carrier that had not been officially named was only one name "001A".

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38590852_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### "Big Ship" in the eyes of the locals

Although it was reported many years ago that China was building the first domestic aircraft carrier, the Ministry of Defense of China officially announced the news until the last day of 2015. According to Chinese media, local people in Dalian are used to calling aircraft carriers "big ships." The length of the aircraft carrier is 315 meters, which is equivalent to the length of the three football fields, and its width is 75 meters.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415492_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### In construction

The "001A" aircraft carrier has received a lot of attention during the construction process. The picture is what the ship looks like in February 2017, and there are still many brackets on the hull.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415475_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### Welcome to the anniversary celebration

Previously, it was speculated that the aircraft carrier was likely to launch the water on April 23, 2017. Because this day is the 68th anniversary of the founding of the Chinese People's Liberation Army. It is also reported that Xi Jinping, the chairman of the Central Military Commission, may personally attend the waters of the ship. But on April 26, Fan Changlong, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and vice chairman of the Central Military Commission.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415443_303.jpg)

### "Boss" Liaoning

The Chinese Navy's only active aircraft carrier "Liaoning" is rebuilt on the basis of the "Warkeg" manufactured by Ukraine. Some experts believe that the "Liaoning" is not an aircraft carrier that can really be used for military operations, but a platform for exercise and training and conducts one -step research and development.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415557_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

###

At the end of 2016, the "Liaoning" conducted drills in the South China Sea and "detoured Taiwan" on the way, causing international attention. However, Taiwan media quoted military people and pointed out that Liaoning did not have all -weather combat capabilities. If you put it into actual combat, you can only play 30 % of the combat power.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415538_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### The third aircraft carrier?

In addition to the "Liaoning" and "Shandong", China currently has the third aircraft carrier -but its role is only used to entertain and recreational. The former Soviet Navy's "Minsk" sold to China after retiring in the late 1990s, and was transformed into a military theme park in Shenzhen.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38415522_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

### "Small step fast run"

In 2016, the ship was dragged to Zhoushan to renovate, and it is said that it will settle in Nantong, Jiangsu in the future. As for the real third aircraft carrier of the Chinese Navy, it is reported that it is built by Shanghai Jiangnan Shipyard. Chinese military expert, Major General Xu Guangyu, told the media that the development strategy of Chinese aircraft carriers is "small steps" and will realize nuclear -powered aircraft carriers in the future.

*![](Images/dwzh/2023-05-27T11-01-00Z/38356895_303.jpg)#
####  China's first domestic aircraft carrier "Shandong" officially delivered to the Navy

####

Although China has invested heavily in strengthening the navy, there is still a certain gap compared with the United States. The U.S. military currently has ten active aircraft carriers, including the recently sailing to the Korean Peninsula. The latest generation of three "Ford -class" nuclear -powered aircraft carriers are also under construction, with a total length of 337 meters, a width of 78 meters, and a displacement of up to 100,000 tons (the corresponding data of the 001A type are 315 meters, 75 meters, and 70,000 tons).

