In 2019's "Counterfeit" Movement, the Citizen Party plays an important role. With the implementation of the Hong Kong National Security Law in 2020, the Citizenship's Legislative Council or District Councilor members were either retired from the party or they were seized or resigned to show dissatisfaction.

The Hong Kong Democratic School issued an unofficial "Legislative Council Primary Election" in 2020. Subsequently, 47 participants, including 4 Citizen Party members, were charged with "conspiracy to subvert the state power."

